<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbe-editions" aria-labelledby="qbe-editions-heading" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The six industry editions</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" id="qbe-editions-heading" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Enterprise tuned to your industry.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Each edition ships with industry-specific chart of accounts templates, reports, and workflow features. Starting in the right one saves significant rework later &mdash; though you can switch editions if needed. Not sure which fits? <a href="/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review">Start with a free file review</a> &mdash; no commission, an honest answer.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for e in editions %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ e.tier }}</span><h3>{{ e.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ e.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal" id="qbe-fit" aria-labelledby="qbe-fit-heading">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Who QuickBooks Enterprise fits</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" id="qbe-fit-heading" style="margin-bottom:10px;">The businesses Enterprise genuinely serves well.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Enterprise is the right answer for a specific kind of mid-market business. These are the situations where it&rsquo;s a clear win.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for f in fit %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ f.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ f.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbe-not-fit" aria-labelledby="qbe-not-fit-heading" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">When Enterprise isn&rsquo;t the right call</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" id="qbe-not-fit-heading" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Two directions to look instead.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Enterprise is the right answer for a specific business profile. If you&rsquo;re not in that profile, the right answer is either down to QBO &mdash; or up to a real ERP.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for n in notFit %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ n.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ n.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal" id="qbe-tiers" aria-labelledby="qbe-tiers-heading">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Enterprise subscription tiers</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" id="qbe-tiers-heading" style="margin-bottom:10px;">What tier levels actually mean.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Intuit structures Enterprise with multiple subscription tier levels offering different bundles. Tier names and inclusions have shifted over time &mdash; verify current structure with Intuit &mdash; but the typical bundling pattern is consistent.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for t in tiers %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ t.num }}</span><h3>{{ t.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ t.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbe-services" aria-labelledby="qbe-services-heading" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">How we support Enterprise businesses</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" id="qbe-services-heading" style="margin-bottom:10px;">From fit assessment to ongoing operations.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">TechBrot ProAdvisors handle the full Enterprise lifecycle &mdash; selection, setup, ongoing operations, and the eventual platform decision when you outgrow it.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for s in services %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ s.num }}</span><h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal" id="qbe-routing">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Your situation</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:24px;">Where are you with QuickBooks Enterprise?</h2>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for b in routing %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ b.href }}"><h3>{{ b.opener | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ b.body | safe }}</p><span class="hub-card__go">{{ b.cta | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qbe-operator" aria-labelledby="qbe-operator-heading" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Who performs the work</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" id="qbe-operator-heading" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Enterprise-Certified ProAdvisor. Honest, top to bottom.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Every TechBrot Enterprise engagement is delivered by a Certified ProAdvisor with active Enterprise credentials &mdash; not a general bookkeeper who&rsquo;s worked in Enterprise a few times. The product&rsquo;s features (advanced inventory, custom roles, ODBC, industry editions) only deliver value when configured by someone who understands them deeply.</p>
      <p>We earn nothing from your Enterprise subscription &mdash; no Intuit referral fees, no affiliate revenue, no commission. The recommendation you get reflects what fits your business, not what pays us. That includes telling you Enterprise is wrong when it is &mdash; either over-spec for your needs or below your ceiling. You can <a href="/quickbooks/proadvisor-team/">meet the ProAdvisor team</a> or read our <a href="/trust/">trust &amp; methodology standards</a>. Independent ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row" style="margin-top:22px;">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal" id="qbe-related" aria-labelledby="qbe-related-heading">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Other QuickBooks products</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" id="qbe-related-heading" style="margin-bottom:24px;">If Enterprise isn&rsquo;t the right answer.</h2>
    {%- for n in related %}
    <div style="margin-bottom:18px;">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
